metadata.name: Emend 115 mg 5mL Injection powder lyophilized for solution

clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: For the prevention of nausea and vomiting associated with highly emetogenic cancer chemotherapy

contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Fosaprepitant is a prodrug of Aprepitant Once biologically activated the drug acts as a substance P neurokinin 1 NK1 receptor antagonist which in combination with other antiemetic agents is indicated for the prevention of acute and delayed nausea and vomiting associated with initial and repeat courses of highly emetogenic cancer chemotherapy Aprepitant is a selective high affinity antagonist of human substance P neurokinin 1 NK1 receptors Aprepitant has little or no affinity for serotonin 5 HT sub 3 sub dopamine and corticosteroid receptors the targets of existing therapies for chemotherapy induced nausea and vomiting CI NV
